UID:10005127-1775151000-1775154600@mohai.org
SUMMARY:Living Voices: Winning Her Wings
DESCRIPTION:They flew planes. They fought prejudice. They made history. Winning Her Wings brings to life the groundbreaking Women Airforce Service Pilots (WASPs). Follow journeys of women who faced and broke barriers together\, fighting for justice in a time of global conflict and domestic prejudice. Discover how they soared—despite the odds. \nThis new multimedia performance by Living Voices blends live theatre and archival film to honor the women who served with courage. Premiering in 2026 for Women’s History Month. This event takes place during our Free First Thursday hours. Seats are first come first served. \nLiving Voices combines live theatrical performances with archival film\, turning history into a moving personal journey. This performance will take place in the Joshua Green Foundation Theater on MOHAI’s second floor.
URL:https://mohai.org/event/living-voices-winning-her-wings/2026-04-02/1/
LOCATION:Joshua Green Foundation Theater\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, WA\, 98109\, United States
CATEGORIES:History,People & Culture
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mohai.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Living-Voices-Winning-Her-Wings_Hero.jpg
END:VEVENT
