SUMMARY:Paving the Way: Bicycle Infrastructure Tour
DESCRIPTION:Join Merlin Rainwater\, creator of Seattle’s Infamous Redline Guide\, and Tom Fucoloro\, Founder and Editor of the Seattle Bike Blog and author of Biking Uphill in the Rain: The Story of Seattle from behind the Handlebars\, for a bicycle tour exploring the history of Seattle bicycle infrastructure. \nThis tour requires riding a bicycle between multiple sites in Seattle\, totaling close to 10 miles and starting in the Central District. Please bring your own bike. Helmets and lights will be required. For any accessibility support\, or general inquiries\, email programs@mohai.org.
URL:https://mohai.org/event/paving-the-way-bicycle-infrastructure-tour/
LOCATION:Offsite
CATEGORIES:Civics,History,Hobbies,Infrastructure,Neighborhoods,People & Culture
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mohai.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Bicycle-Infrastructure-Tour_Hero.jpg
END:VEVENT
