SUMMARY:History Café: Field Notes Podcast
DESCRIPTION:Join HistoryLink’s Tony Williams for a live recording of the Field Notes podcast featuring UW Architecture Professor Vikram Prakash. We’re digging into the intersection of deep time and urban design to discover how Seattle’s geological past continues to shape its future. \nHistory Café is produced as a partnership between HistoryLink\, The Pacific Northwest Historians Guild\, and MOHAI. \nASL Interpretation and CART captioning are available during the program. In addition\, a limited number of Assistive Listening Devices are available upon request. For more accessibility support\, email programs@mohai.org before the program. \nGrab some food for thought–complimentary snacks and beverages will be provided. \nIf you can’t make it to the museum\, tune in live on the MOHAI YouTube channel to virtually attend this event.
URL:https://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-field-notes-podcast/
LOCATION:Faye G. Allen Grand Atrium\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, WA\, 98109\, United States
CATEGORIES:Environment,History,Infrastructure,Neighborhoods
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mohai.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Field-Notes-Podcast_Hero.jpg
END:VEVENT
