SUMMARY:Drawing From History: Ripples of Time
DESCRIPTION:Lake Union is haunted by ghosts of the past\, echoing through time. In this class\, participants will explore past\, present\, and future of the Lake Union Watershed by creating quick layered gesture drawings in charcoal\, based off photos and ephemera from MOHAI’s collections. The class will culminate at the water’s edge\, creating a drawing representing visions for the future. \nDrawing From History is offered in partnership with Gage Academy of Art. \nAll art making materials will be provided. Tickets include access to MOHAI’s exhibitions. For accessibility support and general program inquiries\, email programs@mohai.org.
URL:https://mohai.org/event/drawing-from-history-ripples-of-time/
LOCATION:Microsoft Lakefront Pavilion\, MOHAI - 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, WA\, 98109\, United States
CATEGORIES:Art,Entertainment,History,Neighborhoods
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mohai.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Drawing-from-History-Ripples-of-Time_hero.jpg
END:VEVENT
