UID:10005138-1781721000-1781726400@mohai.org
SUMMARY:History Café: Shelf Life Community Story Project
DESCRIPTION:The Shelf Life Community Story Project records oral histories with current and former residents of Seattle’s Central District neighborhood. Join contributors for a talk about their new book\, Limitless: Stories from the Neighborhood that Shaped Seattle\, the culmination of a multi-year oral history project in Seattle’s historically redlined Central District neighborhood. Stories of innovation\, interdependence\, self-determination\, creativity\, and resistance are illustrated by seven artists with roots in the CD. \nHistory Café is produced as a partnership between HistoryLink\, The Pacific Northwest Historians Guild\, and MOHAI. \nASL Interpretation and CART captioning are available during the program. In addition\, a limited number of Assistive Listening Devices are available upon request. For more accessibility support\, email programs@mohai.org before the program. \nGrab some food for thought–complimentary snacks and beverages will be provided. \nIf you can’t make it to the museum\, tune in live on the MOHAI YouTube channel to virtually attend this event.
URL:https://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-shelf-life-community-story-project/
LOCATION:Faye G. Allen Grand Atrium\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, WA\, 98109\, United States
CATEGORIES:BIPOC,History,Neighborhoods,People & Culture
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mohai.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/shelf-life-community-story-project_hero.jpg
END:VEVENT
